A THREE-MONTH-OLD Marondera baby, Obey Andrea, is seeking assistance to undergo an operation at Parirenyatwa Group of Hospitals to remove a huge growth in his left eye. By Jairos SaunyamaPhoebie Chirau holds her baby, Obey Andrea in her armsHis mother, Phoebie Chirau (28), said Andrea, who was born with the condition, is having sleepless nights, as he is always crying due to the pain.She said the medical team at Parirenyatwa failed to diagnose the condition and wanted to do a CT scan to try to establish the problem. Chirau said the hospital wants $192 for the scan.